Remarks.
Pseudacanthicus major
is known and marketed in ornamental fish trade, like others species of the genus.
Pseudacanthicus major
is recognized in the L number system employed by aquarists as L186 (Schraml & Schaefer, 2004;
Stawikowski et al ., 2004
;
Werner et al ., 2005
). There is no suggestion that the species is consumed as food source by the colonies of fishermen ( pers. obs. )
